ruption between the bounds of infinitely replicating sense and the conceptual vanishing point that is singularity. In examinations of Nancy’s foundational rereading of Descartes's cogito as iterative, his formal experimentations with the genres of philosophical writing, the account of “retreat” in understanding the political, and the interruptive play of sense and singularity in writings on the body, sexuality, and aesthetics, Van Den Abbeele offers a fresh account of one of our major thinkers as well as a provocative inquiry into what philosophy can do.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFinite, The. 0aSense (Philosophy). 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Deconstruction.2bisacsh  aArt and Aesthetics.  aEros and Sexuality.  aFinitude and Philosophy.  aJean-Luc Nancy.  aMind / Body problem.  aPoetry and poetics.  aRetreat of the Political.  aSensible / Intelligible.  aSingularity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishz978311131922308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023z9783111318646oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075167340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781531503321?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781531503321423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781531503321/original  a978-3-11-075167-3  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131922-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 E